=========================================================================
BUG 4:

Segmentation fault parsing erpmenu.4gl
---------------------------------------

[root@aptiva erp]# cd src/utility/
[root@aptiva utility]# p4gl --file=erpmenu.4gl --database=p4gl_repository  --insert
Segmentation fault

=========================================================================
BUG 5:


Invoking fgldoc after action like :

/usr/local/bin/fgldoc --ui=CUI --action=importFgl
 --import_directory=/opt/aubit/apps/erp/src/utility --load_recursive
 --package_name=MaxERP --send_line_to_log

starts the same action again and again.

even if you type just:

	"/usr/local/bin/fgldoc"

you get the last action executed, and I would expect to get fgldoc running in GUI mode...


If you then try:

	"/usr/local/bin/fgldoc --help"

you get help OK.

If you try again just:

	"/usr/local/bin/fgldoc"

it behaves like you typed:

/usr/local/bin/fgldoc --ui=CUI --action=importFgl
 --import_directory=/opt/aubit/apps/erp/src/utility --load_recursive
 --package_name=MaxERP --send_line_to_log

 If you type:

 	"/usr/local/bin/fgldoc --ui=GUI"


THEN you get GUI.

And after that, if you try:

	"/usr/local/bin/fgldoc"

You _FINALLY_ get GUI as you would expect...

===========================================================================
BUG 6:

GUI main screen has 5 pictures:

CSV=>db
4gl=>db
CSV=>db (again) <<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<,
db=>4gl
db=>HTML

The duplicated CSV=>db should be db=>CSV


===========================================================================
BUG 7:

TEST:Unit perl module is not checked in configure

===========================================================================
BUG 8:

There should exist an option that parses a 4gl source tree and generate on
the fly the static html files of the project.

Something like:
   fgldoc --parse_and_document

And using all the other parameters to know where and what to do.

===========================================================================
BUG 9:

By default fgldoc should work on the current directory recursively.
===========================================================================



